parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and failure of the subframe can cause loss of handling, leading to accidents, and render the vehicle immobile.
symptoms: The vehicle swerves off the road
the rear end jerks sideways
the vehicle makes a loud clanking or banging sound
the shock absorber becomes detached
and the vehicle is unable to drive safely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust corrosion of the subframe and body can cause the vehicle to become unstable and potentially lead to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Rust holes in the wheel wells
shock towers
and subframe; loud noises while driving; uneven tire wear; loose or detached body panels; and loss of vehicle stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door hinges and latches can cause the doors to detach from the vehicle while in motion, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Doors that will not close or latch properly; loose or detached door hinges; and loud noises while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or stiff
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the pedal sticks to the floorboard
the vehicle hesitates or stalls
and the pedal requires multiple attempts to depress.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the accelerator pedal to stick, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or stiff
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the pedal sticks to the floorboard
the vehicle hesitates or stalls
and the pedal requires multiple attempts to depress.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
